    <introduction>
      <Value><![CDATA[<p>Queen Margaret University (QMU) is hosting a truly unique dining experience with dishes prepared by a team of talented chefs from some of Scotland’s leading hotels. This gastronomic extravaganza, which will take place on the 13 November, is the final run-through of The Scottish Culinary Team’s menu for the 2018 Culinary World Cup. These culinary champions, in the making, have been perfecting these dishes over the last 18 months whilst getting competition ready. The dinner will be attended by Albert Roux OBE, KFO who is a Patron of Scottish Chefs and a champion for Scottish Food and Drink.</p>]]></Value>
